abstract: Camaraderie characterizes nearly every crisis that New Yorkers collectively endure, but the transit strike has brought an added intimacy. Commuters are walking across bridges together, standing in lines at bicycle shops and roller skating side by side down Broadway. The result is that love affairs have begun blossoming in the streets.
headline_main: Some Walks Lead to Romantic Turns
